# RFID Inventory Project — Context

## Goal
A barebones desktop app that reads UHF RFID tags with a handheld reader and
auto-populates a Google Sheet with inventory data (per-SKU counts + a scan log).

## Hardware
- Reader: **Vulcan RFID Indium** Bluetooth UHF handheld. Under the hood it is a
  **rebadged TSL 1128** (confirmed by the USB device name `usbserial-1128_US_V01336`).
- Protocol: **TSL ASCII 2.0**. Commands are a period + two lowercase letters
  (e.g. `.iv` inventory, `.vr` version, `.rd` read, `.ws` write single), terminated
  with CR/LF.
- Tags: EPC Class 1 Gen 2 (ISO 18000-6C), 902–928 MHz (US).

## ASCII 2.0 response format
Line-based. Inventory (`.iv`) returns:
```
CS: .iv ...                      # command echoed back
EP: 41524E4C3030303030310000     # one EP: line per transponder (the EPC, hex)
EP: 330DE29525C0210005F5F8F2
OK:                              # or "ER: nnn" on failure
```
Parsing rule: collect each value after an `EP:` header until `OK:`/`ER:`.
Other possible per-tag fields (off by default): `IX:` index, `RI:` RSSI, `PC:`,
`CR:` CRC. Default trigger press also runs `.iv`.

## Platform / connection (macOS)
- Running on a Mac. The reader exposes two serial ports:
  - `/dev/cu.usbserial-1128_US_V01336`  → USB  (preferred — stable, no pairing)
  - `/dev/cu.V01336-US-Indium`          → Bluetooth SPP
- Use the **USB** port. Over USB the reader always speaks ASCII 2.0.
- macOS classic-Bluetooth SPP is unreliable for serial; avoid unless USB unavailable.
- pyserial baud: try 115200 first, fall back to 9600 if no response.

## Critical design principle — UHF dedup
UHF readers re-read the same tag many times per second. NEVER count raw reads.
Collect DISTINCT EPCs into a `set()`. One unique EPC == one physical item, so a
SKU's quantity == number of distinct EPCs seen for it in a scan session.

## Google Sheets
- Library: `gspread` with a **service account** (`credentials.json` next to the script).
- Enable BOTH the Google Sheets API and Google Drive API (gspread opens by name).
- Share the spreadsheet with the service account's `client_email` as Editor.
- Worksheet layout (auto-created if missing):
  - `Mapping`:   EPC | SKU | Item Name | Registered At
  - `Inventory`: SKU | Item Name | Quantity | Last Counted
  - `Log`:       Timestamp | EPC | SKU

## App structure (see rfid_inventory.py)
- Menu loop: [1] Enroll a tag  [2] Run inventory count  [3] Quit
- Enroll: `.iv -fs on` (strongest tag only) -> prompt for SKU/name -> write Mapping.
- Count: repeatedly issue `.iv` for SWEEP_SECONDS, accumulate unique EPCs, resolve
  via Mapping, write per-SKU counts to Inventory + rows to Log. Unknown EPCs flagged.

